The paper discusses learning-based hashing methods for large-scale embedding, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on image classification and retrieval, cs.CV is the most likely category. The use of manifold learning techniques also suggests cs.LG and cs.AI as likely categories. The mention of semantic retrieval performance indicates cs.IR as a possible category, while the use of short code lengths suggests cs.CL as a less likely but still possible category.
